  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support and inclusion of children with disabilities and caregivers in CP service delivery in North East Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving child protection assistance internally displaced persons, returnees and host community members in Adamawa, Borno and Yobe. This UNICEF project seeks to improve access to inclusive, equal, timely and safe access to child protection services for boys and girls with disabilities. This project assesses the needs of children with disabilities; provides tailored support; facilitates access to education and child-friendly safe spaces; and distributes dignity kits. The project provides life-saving assistance to 7,100 people, including 450 women, 450 men, 6,200 children, and 3,100 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
